clearDrc(25.10)                                                clearDrc(25.10)

Name
       clearDrc - Clears all design rule checking (DRC) markers in your design

Syntax
        clearDrc [-help]

       Clears all design rule checking (DRC) markers in your design.

       Note:  Do  not  use  the  clearDrc command before using ecoRoute or any
       other routing command. This is because NanoRoute works only on the  ex-
       isting DRC/violation markers. The routing commands will not necessarily
       perform DRC checks in the routing halo regions if the violation markers
       are already cleared.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description of the clearDrc command usage.

              For a detailed description of the command, use the man command:

              man clearDrc

Related Information
              * verify_drc

              * The Identifying and Viewing Violations chapter of User Guide.

